Procurement is the act of acquiring, buying goods, services or works from an external source, often via a tendering or bid process. It is favourable that the goods, services or works are appropriate and that they are procured at the best possible cost to meet the needs of the acquirer in terms of quality and quantity, time, and location. Corporations and public bodies often define processes intended to promote fair and open competition for their business while minimizing exposure to fraud and collusion.

The Enterprise Context Diagram is a Business Architecture artifact that provides a single view of the key stakeholders and processes involved in the business. It also establishes a framework to further breakdown and understand the business.
Enterprise Context Diagrams show how the enterprise exists in the context of processes and business actors around it. The enterprise context is the process of identifying internal and external environmental trends, articulating the business strategy, identifying requirements, creating principles and developing anchor models of the business.
